*The Conditions of “Lā ilāha illa Allāh” in detail:*

== 1. Knowledge -- Opposite of Ignorance

Meaning: To truly understand the meaning of _Lā ilāha illa Allāh_, both its negation and affirmation.

Evidence:

#quran-block[
  فَٱعۡلَمۡ أَنَّهُۥ لَآ إِلَٰهَ إِلَّا ٱللَّهُ وَٱسۡتَغۡفِرۡ لِذَنۢبِكَ
  وَلِلۡمُؤۡمِنِينَ وَٱلۡمُؤۡمِنَٰتِۗ وَٱللَّهُ يَعۡلَمُ مُتَقَلَّبَكُمۡ
  وَمَثۡوَىٰكُمۡ ١٩
][
  #sc[So know that there is no god worthy of worship but Allāh] and ask
  forgiveness for your sin and for the believing men and believing women. And
  Allāh knows of your movement and your resting place... (Muḥammad Q47:19)
]

== 2. Certainty -- Opposite of Doubt

Meaning: The one who says it must be fully certain, without any doubt, that
Allāh alone is the true One worthy of worship.

Evidence:

#quran-block[
  إِنَّمَا ٱلۡمُؤۡمِنُونَ ٱلَّذِينَ ءَامَنُواْ بِٱللَّهِ وَرَسُولِهِۦ ثُمَّ لَمۡ
  يَرۡتَابُواْ وَجَٰهَدُواْ بِأَمۡوَٰلِهِمۡ وَأَنفُسِهِمۡ فِي سَبِيلِ ٱللَّهِۚ
  أُوْلَٰٓئِكَ هُمُ ٱلصَّٰدِقُونَ ١٥
][
  #sc[The true believers are only those who believe in Allāh and His Messenger and
  then have no doubt] and who strive with their wealth and lives in Allāh's cause.
  It is they who are truthful.” (Al-Ḥujurāt Q49:15)
]

== 3. Sincerity -- Opposite of Shirk (associating partners with Allāh)

Meaning: To direct all acts of worship purely to Allāh, without giving any part
of them to anyone or anything else.

Evidence:

#quran-block[
  وَمَآ أُمِرُوٓاْ إِلَّا لِيَعۡبُدُواْ ٱللَّهَ مُخۡلِصِينَ لَهُ ٱلدِّينَ
  حُنَفَآءَ وَيُقِيمُواْ ٱلصَّلَوٰةَ وَيُؤۡتُواْ ٱلزَّكَوٰةَۚ وَذَٰلِكَ دِينُ
  ٱلۡقَيِّمَةِ ٥
][
  #sc[And they were not commanded except to worship Allāh, [being] sincere to Him
  in religion,] inclining to truth, and to establish prayer and to give _zakāh_.
  And that is the correct religion.” (Al-Bayyinah Q98:5)
]

== 4. Truthfulness -- Opposite of Lying

Meaning: To say the testimony of faith honestly, with your heart matching your
words.

Evidence:

#quran-block[
  أَحَسِبَ ٱلنَّاسُ أَن يُتۡرَكُوٓاْ أَن يَقُولُوٓاْ ءَامَنَّا وَهُمۡ لَا
  يُفۡتَنُونَ ٢ وَلَقَدۡ فَتَنَّا ٱلَّذِينَ مِن قَبۡلِهِمۡۖ فَلَيَعۡلَمَنَّ
  ٱللَّهُ ٱلَّذِينَ صَدَقُواْ وَلَيَعۡلَمَنَّ ٱلۡكَٰذِبِينَ ٣
][
  Do people think they will be left alone after saying, “We believe,” without
  being tested? We certainly tested those before them. #sc[And Allāh will surely
  make evident those who are truthful,] and He will surely expose the liars.
  (Al-ʿAnkabūt Q29:2--3)
]

== 5. Love -- Opposite of Hatred

Meaning: You must say _Lā ilāha illa Allāh_ while loving Allāh, His Messenger
#pbuh and this statement itself -- loving everything it stands for.

Evidence:

#quran-block[
  وَمِنَ ٱلنَّاسِ مَن يَتَّخِذُ مِن دُونِ ٱللَّهِ أَندَادٗا يُحِبُّونَهُمۡ
  كَحُبِّ ٱللَّهِۖ وَٱلَّذِينَ ءَامَنُوٓاْ أَشَدُّ حُبّٗا لِّلَّهِۗ وَلَوۡ يَرَى
  ٱلَّذِينَ ظَلَمُوٓاْ إِذۡ يَرَوۡنَ ٱلۡعَذَابَ أَنَّ ٱلۡقُوَّةَ لِلَّهِ
  جَمِيعٗا وَأَنَّ ٱللَّهَ شَدِيدُ ٱلۡعَذَابِ ١٦٥
][
  And among people are those who take others besides Allāh as equals -- they love
  them as they should love Allāh. #sc[But those who believe are stronger in their
  love for Allāh] And if only they who have wronged would consider [that] when
  they see the punishment, [they will be certain] that all power belongs to Allāh
  and that Allāh is severe in punishment... (Al-Baqarah Q2:165)
]

== 6. Submission -- Opposite of neglect or refusal to act

Meaning: To worship Allāh alone, submit fully to His commands, accept His laws,
and believe that they are the truth.

Evidence:

#quran-block[
  وَأَنِيبُوٓاْ إِلَىٰ رَبِّكُمۡ وَأَسۡلِمُواْ لَهُۥ مِن قَبۡلِ أَن يَأۡتِيَكُمُ
  ٱلۡعَذَابُ ثُمَّ لَا تُنصَرُونَ ٥٤
][
  #sc[Turn to your Lord and submit to Him] before the torment comes upon you, then
  (otherwise) you will not be helped. (Al-Zumar Q39:54)
]

== 7. Acceptance -- Opposite of Denial or Rejection

Meaning: To accept _Lā ilāha illa Allāh_ sincerely, and accept what it means:
devoting worship to Allāh alone and rejecting worship of all others.

Evidence:

#quran-block[
  إِنَّهُمۡ كَانُوٓاْ إِذَا قِيلَ لَهُمۡ لَآ إِلَٰهَ إِلَّا ٱللَّهُ
  يَسۡتَكۡبِرُونَ ٣٥ وَيَقُولُونَ أَئِنَّا لَتَارِكُوٓاْ ءَالِهَتِنَا لِشَاعِرٖ
  مَّجۡنُونِۭ ٣٦
][
  #sc[Indeed, when it was said to them, “There is no god worthy of worship but
  Allāh,” they acted arrogantly] and said, “Should we really abandon our gods for
  a mad poet?” (Al-Ṣāffāt Q37:35--6)
]

== 8. Disbelief in What is Worshipped Besides Allāh

Meaning: You must reject and disown all false gods and everything worshipped
besides Allāh, and believe that such worship is false.

Evidence:

#quran-block[
  لَآ إِكۡرَاهَ فِي ٱلدِّينِۖ قَد تَّبَيَّنَ ٱلرُّشۡدُ مِنَ ٱلۡغَيِّۚ فَمَن
  يَكۡفُرۡ بِٱلطَّٰغُوتِ وَيُؤۡمِنۢ بِٱللَّهِ فَقَدِ ٱسۡتَمۡسَكَ بِٱلۡعُرۡوَةِ
  ٱلۡوُثۡقَىٰ لَا ٱنفِصَامَ لَهَاۗ وَٱللَّهُ سَمِيعٌ عَلِيمٌ ٢٥٦
][
  There is no compulsion in religion. Verily, the Right Path has become distinct
  from the wrong path. #sc[Whoever disbelieves in Taghūt and believes in Allāh,
  then he has grasped the most trustworthy handhold that will never break. And
  Allāh is All-Hearer, All-Knower.] (Al-Baqarah Q2:256)
]